                            <comment id="481323" author="sebastien" created="Mon, 15 Dec 2025 07:53:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=utopiabound&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;utopiabound&quot;&gt;utopiabound&lt;/a&gt; so if I understand you correctly, having a Rust binding to the C llapi using Rust&apos;s FFI (and generated bindings) would not be enough? Does it mean you would want a Rust crate wrapping the C llapi?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="481242" author="utopiabound" created="Fri, 12 Dec 2025 17:39:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We experimented with llapi at one point but it caused some problems with the build pipeline because every build target needed lustre libraries/headers to build against, so we currently don&apos;t build against llapi and solely use CLI calls.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Pie in the sky request would be a pure rust llapi implementation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="480956" author="JIRAUSER18716" created="Wed, 10 Dec 2025 15:42:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=utopiabound&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;utopiabound&quot;&gt;utopiabound&lt;/a&gt; any requests for nodemap related functions ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="480754" author="sebastien" created="Tue, 9 Dec 2025 13:52:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The idea is to be able to carry out all &apos;lctl nodemap&amp;#42;&apos; commands but programmatically via the llapi. Ideally, the associated &apos;lctl nodemap&amp;#42;&apos; commands would be modified to internally call the corresponding llapi functions. That would make the llapi central and used internally by userspace commands.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
